<!-- ============ FAQ ============ -->
<section class="section" style="padding-bottom: 80px;">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Frequently Asked Questions</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Everything you need to know.</h2>
    </div>
    <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          What makes Teamwork Commerce OMS different from standalone order management systems?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Teamwork's OMS is natively integrated with POS, Inventory, and RFID — not bolted on through middleware. Order-fill decisions run on RFID-verified real-time stock (99.9% accuracy), not stale batch-synced data. You configure the fill logic — ranking strategies by shipping cost, stock depth, proximity, and store capacity — so every order is routed for margin, not just speed.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          How does Order Fill Logic decide where to fulfill an order?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Order Fill Logic is a ranked, configurable rule stack. You set the priority — for example, fill complete from the highest-stock location, ship-to-store for pickup orders, or ship-from-vendor — and the engine applies your rules to every order using RFID-verified stock, shipping cost, and proximity. It can also split an order across nodes when a single location can't fill it.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          Can Teamwork Commerce OMS handle ship-from-store and BOPIS?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. Ship-from-store turns every retail location into a fulfillment node with pick-and-pack tasks for store associates. BOPIS (Buy Online Pick Up In Store) is backed by RFID-verified stock — eliminating the 60% failure rate that plagues retailers relying on barcode-based inventory. Curbside pickup and Buy Online Return In Store (BORIS) are also natively supported.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          How does Teamwork Commerce OMS compare to New Black EVA and NewStore?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>New Black EVA offers scoring-based order orchestration but requires third-party middleware for RFID. NewStore focuses heavily on fulfillment but doesn't offer native RFID or merchandising intelligence. Teamwork Commerce uniquely combines configurable Order Fill Logic, the industry's only native end-to-end RFID stack (so routing runs on 99.9% accurate inventory), and 30+ years of retail expertise — all in one system, no middleware required.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          Does the OMS support multi-currency and multi-entity operations?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. The OMS operates across multiple legal entities, currencies, and tax jurisdictions. A US-based HQ can manage global operations while regional teams see dashboards in their local currency and language. Automated VAT, GST, and sales tax calculations ensure cross-border fulfillment is always compliant.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

